This paper deals with the problem of reconfiguring dominating sets in a graph, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (DM) and graph theory (GT). The problem is related to the complexity of algorithms (DS) and computational complexity (CC). The paper also mentions specific types of graphs, such as split, bipartite, and bounded tree-width graphs, which are common topics in computational geometry (CG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.GT, and cs.CG, in that order.
